SYNOPSIS

    Use directly:

     use Media::Info::Mplayer qw(get_media_info);
     my $res = get_media_info(media => '/home/steven/celine.avi');

    or use via Media::Info.

    Sample result:

     [
       200,
       "OK",
       {
         audio_bitrate => 128000,
         audio_format  => 85,
         audio_rate    => 44100,
         duration      => 2081.25,
         num_channels  => 2,
         num_chapters  => 0,
       },
       {
         "func.raw_output" => "ID_AUDIO_ID=0\n...",
       },
     ]

SEE ALSO

    Media::Info

